</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e6a38779e65b4c5991ae7ccf30b9487a449b0421" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:5.271ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle 2\ln n}"></span>, and the whole tree has <a href="/wiki/Logarithm" title="Logarithm">logarithmic</a> depth (its maximum root-to-leaf distance) <a href="/wiki/With_high_probability" title="With high probability">with high probability</a>. More formally, there exists a constant <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle C}">
